Kenya Breweries Limited, through the Tusker trademark, will next month begin the first-ever OktobaBeer Festival, which will run for two days. The festival will run from October 5-6 at Ngong Racecourse and will have an all-Kenyan entertainment line-up of 39 acts. These include Khaligraph Jones, Sauti Sol, Nyashinksi, Jua Cali, Fena, The Kansoul, Bensoul, Nadia Mukami, Sailors, Ethic, Ochunglo Family and H_art the band. The event will give beer lovers a chance to taste and experience KBL beers paired with food and music. Revellers will also have plenty of games to enjoy, including arcade basketball, paintball, horse racing, golf, five-aside football and touch rugby.